==English==

===Adverb===
'''allegretto'''

===Etymology===
Borrowed from Italian ''allegretto'', [[diminutive]] form of ''allegro''.

===Meanings===
#''Music.'' A direction in musical notation indicating that the musical piece should be played rather fast and lively.

===Related Terms===

*[[allegrissimo]]
*[[allegro]]

